    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6211/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-21T00:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 21, 1939—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received August 21—10:50
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>852. The German official telegraphic agency and the German radio system has just
                    announced that, “The German and Soviet Governments had agreed to conclude a
                    non-aggression pact with each other” and that “Ribbentrop would arrive in Moscow
                    on Wednesday, August 23, to conclude the negotiations”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
